<br>
Har har har ... yer such a kidder, Ennya! When ya shouted out across the entire zone of Shadowhaven that ya had four stacks of lavarocks sitting around, and did I want 'em ... ya've never seen a dwarf scuttle outta meditation quicker than I did.<br>
<br>
Yegads, I practically told one of me ranger companions tae find ya on track, before I realized that more than likely ya were pullin' me quite short (but now far better rendered) leg. Har har ... smith humor!<br>
<br>
The fact that ya did indeed have two lava rocks and eight drops of mercury ... and that refused ya my meager attempts at paying ya for them ... made me night. If I told ya the plans I've concocted in attempts to secure quantities of those rare storms, ya'd split the seams on yer fine robes laughing ... but then, of course, I'd have hire a Hessian ta silence ya, lest a waggin' tounge give away me secret dwarven smithing techniques!<br>
<br>
I did, however, later in the evening, find somethin' that I'm hoping ya'll let me give ya in return though. I found three vials of swirling mist just sittin' on a bleedin' vendor in the Bazaar. I'll keep me eyes out fer ya in the coming days on Luclin ta intrust these vials to your care.<br>
<br>
Thanks again, Ennya ... <br>
<br>
